-000016168.PNG" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-001823313-03-000016168</illusnum></figure><para translate="yes">Scour the external face of the part at the location of the earth stud:</para><para translate="yes"> <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3478927"><linkdesc>bodywork cleaning tools : description</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001618</linkvalue></sieref>,</para><para translate="yes"> <sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3478796"><linkdesc>paint and rigid adhesive stripping tools : use</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-001617</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descsection></descbody></description><description id="des5" translate="no"><title translate="yes">Welding</title><descbody translate="no"><descsection translate="no"><figure id="fig1"><image dimension="F2 (85x85) #" href="../MergedPictures/ILL-000016184.PNG" style="width: 85.0mm; height: 85.0mm;" translate="no"/><illusnum>RDE-001823313-01-000016184</illusnum><?Pub Caret -1?></figure><para translate="yes">Weld the stud using a resistance welding device equipped with the correct nozzle, using the studs supplied with the welding device.</para><para translate="yes">Manually control the hold of the stud.<sieref href="x-wc://gie=OR:wt.part.WTPartMaster:3503124"><linkdesc>bolted assembly : precautions for the repair</linkdesc><linkvalue>GIEMR-000179</linkvalue></sieref>.</para></descsection></descbody></description></description></description>